  "prompt": "What is the salary of an RTO officer?",
  "response": "The salary of a Regional Transport Officer (RTO) can vary significantly depending on the country, region, level of experience, and specific government regulations. For example, in India, an RTO officer's salary might range from \u20b940,000 to \u20b960,000 per month for entry-level positions, and can increase with experience, seniority, and promotions. Additional benefits such as allowances and bonuses might also be included.\n\nFor accurate and updated information, it's best to refer to official government sources or specific regional transport department guidelines in the relevant area or country.",
